    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "When should I call an emergency electrician in Brampton?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Call an emergency electrician if you notice sparks, smoke, a burning smell, repeated breaker trips, partial power loss, buzzing from the panel, damaged wiring, or water near outlets, switches, appliances, or electrical panels.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "What should I do before an emergency electrician arrives?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "If it is safe, stop using the affected outlet, switch, appliance, or fixture and turn off the related breaker. Do not touch wet electrical equipment, exposed wiring, or a panel that smells hot.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can a breaker that keeps tripping be an emergency?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "A breaker that trips repeatedly can point to an overload, damaged wiring, appliance trouble, or panel concern. If it trips again after resetting once, stop resetting it and call for electrical help.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Do you help with power loss in part of the home?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. Fateh Plumbing & Electric helps troubleshoot partial power loss, dead outlets, failed switches, tripped breakers, panel concerns, and wiring issues in Brampton homes and businesses.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can you help if an outlet smells hot or sparks?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. Stop using the outlet, unplug devices if it is safe, and call for service. A hot, sparking, loose, or damaged outlet should be checked before it is used again.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
