      <h2>What to do before the electrician arrives</h2>
      <p>If the issue is active, stay calm and stop using the affected device or circuit. If it is safe, switch off the related breaker. Do not keep resetting a breaker that trips. Do not touch exposed wiring, wet electrical equipment, or a panel that smells hot.</p>
      <p>Move people away from the area, keep children and pets clear, and avoid using extension cords as a temporary fix for a serious electrical issue. If there is fire, smoke, or immediate danger, call emergency services first.</p>
    </div>
