  <section class="band faq">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Emergency electrician FAQ</p>
      <h2>Common questions before calling an emergency electrician</h2>
    </div>
    <details><summary>When should I call an emergency electrician in Brampton?</summary><p>Call right away for sparks, smoke, burning smells, repeated breaker trips, partial power loss, hot outlets, buzzing panels, damaged wiring, exposed wiring, or water near electrical equipment.</p></details>
    <details><summary>What should I do before the electrician arrives?</summary><p>If it is safe, stop using the affected device and turn off the related breaker. Do not touch exposed wiring, wet electrical equipment, or a panel that smells hot.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Is a breaker that keeps tripping dangerous?</summary><p>A breaker that trips repeatedly can be a sign of overload, damaged wiring, a faulty device, or a panel issue. Do not keep resetting it. Call for electrical troubleshooting.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Can you help with power loss in part of the house?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh helps troubleshoot partial power loss, dead outlets, failed switches, tripped breakers, panel issues, wiring problems, and urgent electrical safety concerns.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Should I use an outlet if it feels hot?</summary><p>No. Stop using the outlet, unplug devices if it is safe, and call for service. A hot, sparking, loose, buzzing, or discolored outlet should be checked before use.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Do you handle emergency electrical service for businesses?</summary><p>Yes. Fateh helps restaurants, retail units, offices, small businesses, landlords, and property managers with urgent electrical issues and safety concerns.</p></details>
    <details><summary>Which Brampton areas do you serve?</summary><p>Fateh serves Brampton areas including Bramalea, Springdale, Castlemore, Mount Pleasant, Heart Lake, Fletcher's Meadow, Credit Valley, Peel Village, Downtown Brampton, and nearby communities.</p></details>
  </section>

